[
  {
    "text": "Last year ...",
    "start": 12.942,
    "duration": 1.691
  },
  {
    "text": "was hell.",
    "start": 14.657,
    "duration": 1.203
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 15.884,
    "duration": 1.798
  },
  {
    "text": "It was my first time eating\nNigerian \"jollof.\"",
    "start": 20.391,
    "duration": 3.552
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 23.967,
    "duration": 1.582
  },
  {
    "text": "Actually, in all seriousness,",
    "start": 26.436,
    "duration": 2.859
  },
  {
    "text": "I was going through a lot\nof personal turmoil.",
    "start": 29.319,
    "duration": 2.814
  },
  {
    "text": "Faced with enormous stress,",
    "start": 33.055,
    "duration": 2.181
  },
  {
    "text": "I suffered an anxiety attack.",
    "start": 35.26,
    "duration": 2.023
  },
  {
    "text": "On some days, I could do no work.",
    "start": 38.362,
    "duration": 2.69
  },
  {
    "text": "On other days,",
    "start": 42.156,
    "duration": 1.896
  },
  {
    "text": "I just wanted to lay in my bed and cry.",
    "start": 44.076,
    "duration": 3.289
  },
  {
    "text": "My doctor asked if I'd like to speak\nwith a mental health professional",
    "start": 48.478,
    "duration": 5.249
  },
  {
    "text": "about my stress and anxiety.",
    "start": 53.751,
    "duration": 2.103
  },
  {
    "text": "Mental health?",
    "start": 56.589,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "I clammed up and violently\nshook my head in protest.",
    "start": 58.792,
    "duration": 3.89
  },
  {
    "text": "I felt a profound sense of a shame.",
    "start": 65.065,
    "duration": 3.752
  },
  {
    "text": "I felt the weight of stigma.",
    "start": 70.233,
    "duration": 3.438
  },
  {
    "text": "I have a loving, supportive family",
    "start": 74.959,
    "duration": 2.359
  },
  {
    "text": "and incredibly loyal friends,",
    "start": 77.342,
    "duration": 2.307
  },
  {
    "text": "yet I could not entertain\nthe idea of speaking to anyone",
    "start": 79.673,
    "duration": 4.569
  },
  {
    "text": "about my feeling of pain.",
    "start": 84.266,
    "duration": 2.03
  },
  {
    "text": "I felt suffocated\nby the rigid architecture",
    "start": 87.824,
    "duration": 4.467
  },
  {
    "text": "of our African masculinity.",
    "start": 92.315,
    "duration": 2.29
  },
  {
    "text": "\"People have real problems, Sangu.",
    "start": 95.585,
    "duration": 2.115
  },
  {
    "text": "Get over yourself!\"",
    "start": 97.724,
    "duration": 1.455
  },
  {
    "text": "The first time I heard \"mental health,\"",
    "start": 100.776,
    "duration": 1.981
  },
  {
    "text": "I was a boarding school student\nfresh off the boat from Ghana,",
    "start": 103.7,
    "duration": 3.963
  },
  {
    "text": "at the Peddie School in New Jersey.",
    "start": 107.687,
    "duration": 1.931
  },
  {
    "text": "I had just gone through\nthe brutal experience",
    "start": 110.887,
    "duration": 3.406
  },
  {
    "text": "of losing seven loved ones\nin the same month.",
    "start": 114.317,
    "duration": 2.553
  },
  {
    "text": "The school nurse,",
    "start": 118.389,
    "duration": 1.456
  },
  {
    "text": "concerned about what I'd gone\nthrough -- God bless her soul --",
    "start": 119.869,
    "duration": 4.064
  },
  {
    "text": "she inquired about my mental health.",
    "start": 123.957,
    "duration": 1.95
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Is she mental?\" I thought.",
    "start": 127.246,
    "duration": 1.983
  },
  {
    "text": "Does she not know I'm an African man?",
    "start": 130.034,
    "duration": 2.444
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 132.502,
    "duration": 1.014
  },
  {
    "text": "Like Okonkwo in \"Things Fall Apart,\"",
    "start": 133.54,
    "duration": 1.871
  },
  {
    "text": "we African men neither process\nnor express our emotions.",
    "start": 135.435,
    "duration": 4.741
  },
  {
    "text": "We deal with our problems.",
    "start": 140.791,
    "duration": 1.691
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 142.506,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "We deal with our problems.",
    "start": 145.001,
    "duration": 1.999
  },
  {
    "text": "I called my brother and laughed\nabout \"Oyibo\" people -- white people --",
    "start": 147.024,
    "duration": 4.771
  },
  {
    "text": "and their strange diseases --",
    "start": 151.819,
    "duration": 1.857
  },
  {
    "text": "depression, ADD and those \"weird things.\"",
    "start": 153.7,
    "duration": 3.238
  },
  {
    "text": "Growing up in West Africa,",
    "start": 158.32,
    "duration": 1.991
  },
  {
    "text": "when people used the term \"mental,\"\nwhat came to mind was a madman",
    "start": 160.335,
    "duration": 4.381
  },
  {
    "text": "with dirty, dread-locked hair,",
    "start": 164.74,
    "duration": 2.243
  },
  {
    "text": "bumbling around half-naked on the streets.",
    "start": 167.007,
    "duration": 2.776
  },
  {
    "text": "We all know this man.",
    "start": 170.904,
    "duration": 1.82
  },
  {
    "text": "Our parents warned us about him.",
    "start": 172.748,
    "duration": 2.281
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Mommy, mommy, why is he mad?\"",
    "start": 175.64,
    "duration": 1.545
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Drugs!",
    "start": 177.209,
    "duration": 1.212
  },
  {
    "text": "If you even look at drugs,\nyou end up like him.\"",
    "start": 178.445,
    "duration": 2.389
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 180.858,
    "duration": 1.189
  },
  {
    "text": "Come down with pneumonia,",
    "start": 182.8,
    "duration": 2.065
  },
  {
    "text": "and your mother will rush you\nto the nearest hospital",
    "start": 184.889,
    "duration": 2.532
  },
  {
    "text": "for medical treatment.",
    "start": 187.445,
    "duration": 1.382
  },
  {
    "text": "But dare to declare depression,",
    "start": 189.91,
    "duration": 2.616
  },
  {
    "text": "and your local pastor\nwill be driving out demons",
    "start": 193.278,
    "duration": 3.402
  },
  {
    "text": "and blaming witches in your village.",
    "start": 196.704,
    "duration": 1.844
  },
  {
    "text": "According to the World\nHealth Organization,",
    "start": 199.118,
    "duration": 2.9
  },
  {
    "text": "mental health is about being able to cope",
    "start": 202.042,
    "duration": 3.058
  },
  {
    "text": "with the normal stressors of life;",
    "start": 205.124,
    "duration": 1.699
  },
  {
    "text": "to work productively and fruitfully;",
    "start": 207.741,
    "duration": 3.443
  },
  {
    "text": "and to be able to make\na contribution to your community.",
    "start": 211.208,
    "duration": 3.627
  },
  {
    "text": "Mental health includes our emotional,\npsychological and social well-being.",
    "start": 215.321,
    "duration": 6.612
  },
  {
    "text": "Globally, 75 percent\nof all mental illness cases",
    "start": 222.676,
    "duration": 4.76
  },
  {
    "text": "can be found in low-income countries.",
    "start": 227.46,
    "duration": 2.634
  },
  {
    "text": "Yet most African governments",
    "start": 230.118,
    "duration": 1.832
  },
  {
    "text": "invest less than one percent\nof their health care budget",
    "start": 231.974,
    "duration": 4.207
  },
  {
    "text": "in mental health.",
    "start": 236.205,
    "duration": 1.276
  },
  {
    "text": "Even worse,",
    "start": 238.501,
    "duration": 1.18
  },
  {
    "text": "we have a severe shortage\nof psychiatrists in Africa.",
    "start": 239.705,
    "duration": 4.119
  },
  {
    "text": "Nigeria, for example,\nis estimated to have 200 --",
    "start": 244.656,
    "duration": 4.283
  },
  {
    "text": "in a country of almost 200 million.",
    "start": 249.632,
    "duration": 3.021
  },
  {
    "text": "In all of Africa,",
    "start": 254.242,
    "duration": 1.469
  },
  {
    "text": "90 percent of our people\nlack access to treatment.",
    "start": 255.735,
    "duration": 3.903
  },
  {
    "text": "As a result,",
    "start": 260.501,
    "duration": 1.753
  },
  {
    "text": "we suffer in solitude,",
    "start": 262.278,
    "duration": 3.004
  },
  {
    "text": "silenced by stigma.",
    "start": 265.306,
    "duration": 2.444
  },
  {
    "text": "We as Africans often respond\nto mental health with distance,",
    "start": 269.318,
    "duration": 4.675
  },
  {
    "text": "ignorance,",
    "start": 274.664,
    "duration": 1.202
  },
  {
    "text": "guilt,",
    "start": 276.355,
    "duration": 1.178
  },
  {
    "text": "fear",
    "start": 277.954,
    "duration": 1.206
  },
  {
    "text": "and anger.",
    "start": 279.754,
    "duration": 1.286
  },
  {
    "text": "In a study conducted by Arboleda-Fl√≥rez,",
    "start": 282.129,
    "duration": 4.677
  },
  {
    "text": "directly asking, \"What is the cause\nof mental illness?\"",
    "start": 286.83,
    "duration": 3.658
  },
  {
    "text": "34 percent of Nigerian respondents\ncited drug misuse;",
    "start": 291.487,
    "duration": 5.284
  },
  {
    "text": "19 percent said divine wrath\nand the will of God --",
    "start": 298.16,
    "duration": 5.184
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 303.368,
    "duration": 1.305
  },
  {
    "text": "12 percent,",
    "start": 305.27,
    "duration": 1.458
  },
  {
    "text": "witchcraft and spiritual possession.",
    "start": 307.95,
    "duration": 2.766
  },
  {
    "text": "But few cited other known\ncauses of mental illness,",
    "start": 311.616,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "like genetics,",
    "start": 316.2,
    "duration": 1.646
  },
  {
    "text": "socioeconomic status,",
    "start": 317.87,
    "duration": 1.936
  },
  {
    "text": "war,",
    "start": 319.83,
    "duration": 1.595
  },
  {
    "text": "conflict",
    "start": 321.449,
    "duration": 1.413
  },
  {
    "text": "or the loss of a loved one.",
    "start": 322.886,
    "duration": 1.515
  },
  {
    "text": "The stigmatization against mental illness",
    "start": 325.829,
    "duration": 2.887
  },
  {
    "text": "often results in the ostracizing\nand demonizing of sufferers.",
    "start": 328.74,
    "duration": 4.466
  },
  {
    "text": "Photojournalist Robin Hammond\nhas documented some of these abuses ...",
    "start": 334.255,
    "duration": 3.996
  },
  {
    "text": "in Uganda,",
    "start": 338.275,
    "duration": 1.393
  },
  {
    "text": "in Somalia,",
    "start": 340.665,
    "duration": 1.329
  },
  {
    "text": "and here in Nigeria.",
    "start": 343.089,
    "duration": 1.829
  },
  {
    "text": "For me,",
    "start": 347.374,
    "duration": 1.342
  },
  {
    "text": "the stigma is personal.",
    "start": 349.877,
    "duration": 2.319
  },
  {
    "text": "In 2009,",
    "start": 353.942,
    "duration": 1.629
  },
  {
    "text": "I received a frantic call\nin the middle of the night.",
    "start": 356.616,
    "duration": 3.106
  },
  {
    "text": "My best friend in the world --",
    "start": 361.179,
    "duration": 2.348
  },
  {
    "text": "a brilliant, philosophical,\ncharming, hip young man --",
    "start": 363.551,
    "duration": 5.139
  },
  {
    "text": "was diagnosed with schizophrenia.",
    "start": 368.714,
    "duration": 2.151
  },
  {
    "text": "I witnessed some of the friends\nwe'd grown up with recoil.",
    "start": 372.424,
    "duration": 4.418
  },
  {
    "text": "I heard the snickers.",
    "start": 379.136,
    "duration": 1.523
  },
  {
    "text": "I heard the whispers.",
    "start": 381.448,
    "duration": 1.592
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Did you hear he has gone mad?\"",
    "start": 384.006,
    "duration": 2.23
  },
  {
    "text": "(Kru English) \"He has gone crazy!\"",
    "start": 387.095,
    "duration": 2.53
  },
  {
    "text": "Derogatory, demeaning commentary\nabout his condition --",
    "start": 389.669,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "words we would never say\nabout someone with cancer",
    "start": 394.013,
    "duration": 3.977
  },
  {
    "text": "or someone with malaria.",
    "start": 398.014,
    "duration": 1.76
  },
  {
    "text": "Somehow, when it comes to mental illness,",
    "start": 400.484,
    "duration": 3.679
  },
  {
    "text": "our ignorance eviscerates all empathy.",
    "start": 404.187,
    "duration": 3.05
  },
  {
    "text": "I stood by his side\nas his community isolated him,",
    "start": 408.539,
    "duration": 4.169
  },
  {
    "text": "but our love never wavered.",
    "start": 413.98,
    "duration": 2.332
  },
  {
    "text": "Tacitly, I became passionate\nabout mental health.",
    "start": 417.668,
    "duration": 3.079
  },
  {
    "text": "Inspired by his plight,",
    "start": 421.694,
    "duration": 2.632
  },
  {
    "text": "I helped found the mental health\nspecial interest alumni group",
    "start": 424.35,
    "duration": 3.323
  },
  {
    "text": "at my college.",
    "start": 427.697,
    "duration": 1.655
  },
  {
    "text": "And during my tenure as a resident\ntutor in graduate school,",
    "start": 429.376,
    "duration": 3.377
  },
  {
    "text": "I supported many undergraduates\nwith their mental health challenges.",
    "start": 432.777,
    "duration": 3.962
  },
  {
    "text": "I saw African students struggle",
    "start": 437.271,
    "duration": 2.515
  },
  {
    "text": "and unable to speak to anyone.",
    "start": 439.81,
    "duration": 1.837
  },
  {
    "text": "Even with this knowledge\nand with their stories in tow,",
    "start": 442.566,
    "duration": 3.996
  },
  {
    "text": "I, in turn, struggled,",
    "start": 446.586,
    "duration": 1.986
  },
  {
    "text": "and could not speak to anyone\nwhen I faced my own anxiety,",
    "start": 448.596,
    "duration": 4.573
  },
  {
    "text": "so deep is our fear of being the madman.",
    "start": 453.193,
    "duration": 3.962
  },
  {
    "text": "All of us --",
    "start": 459.735,
    "duration": 1.198
  },
  {
    "text": "but we Africans especially --",
    "start": 461.698,
    "duration": 2.187
  },
  {
    "text": "need to realize that our mental struggles\ndo not detract from our virility,",
    "start": 464.775,
    "duration": 5.907
  },
  {
    "text": "nor does our trauma taint our strength.",
    "start": 470.706,
    "duration": 2.891
  },
  {
    "text": "We need to see mental health\nas important as physical health.",
    "start": 474.756,
    "duration": 4.709
  },
  {
    "text": "We need to stop suffering in silence.",
    "start": 480.403,
    "duration": 4.403
  },
  {
    "text": "We must stop stigmatizing disease",
    "start": 485.939,
    "duration": 3.458
  },
  {
    "text": "and traumatizing the afflicted.",
    "start": 489.421,
    "duration": 2.206
  },
  {
    "text": "Talk to your friends.",
    "start": 493.399,
    "duration": 1.459
  },
  {
    "text": "Talk to your loved ones.",
    "start": 495.834,
    "duration": 1.576
  },
  {
    "text": "Talk to health professionals.",
    "start": 498.394,
    "duration": 1.765
  },
  {
    "text": "Be vulnerable.",
    "start": 501.437,
    "duration": 1.278
  },
  {
    "text": "Do so with the confidence",
    "start": 503.615,
    "duration": 1.877
  },
  {
    "text": "that you are not alone.",
    "start": 506.335,
    "duration": 2.527
  },
  {
    "text": "Speak up if you're struggling.",
    "start": 510.011,
    "duration": 2.18
  },
  {
    "text": "Being honest about how we feel",
    "start": 514.414,
    "duration": 3.527
  },
  {
    "text": "does not make us weak;",
    "start": 517.965,
    "duration": 1.659
  },
  {
    "text": "it makes us human.",
    "start": 520.629,
    "duration": 1.543
  },
  {
    "text": "It is time to end the stigma\nassociated with mental illness.",
    "start": 523.499,
    "duration": 4.546
  },
  {
    "text": "So the next time your hear \"mental,\"",
    "start": 528.93,
    "duration": 3.411
  },
  {
    "text": "do not just think of the madman.",
    "start": 533.228,
    "duration": 1.995
  },
  {
    "text": "Think of me.",
    "start": 536.163,
    "duration": 1.209
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 537.796,
    "duration": 1.924
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 539.744,
    "duration": 1.283
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 541.051,
    "duration": 3.992
  }
]